om/symbol/ACN/returns)[[1]](https://www.macrotrends.net/stocks/charts/ACN/accenture/stock-price-history)\n- **Vs. Market:** Significantly underperformed S&P 500 (up ~65% over similar period).[[8]](https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/ACN)\n\n### Conclusions & Insights:\n1. **Overall Underperformance:** ACN has been volatile and trended downward over 5 years, driven by sector headwinds. Strong growth in 2021/2023 couldn't offset 2022 bear market and recent slumps.[[7]](https://www.slickcharts.com/symbol/ACN/returns)\n2. **Recent Drivers of Decline (2025–2026):** \n   - Fears of AI disruption reducing demand for traditional consulting/IT services.[[9]](https://www.barrons.com/articles/accenture-earnings-stock-price-8b5d8c09)[[10]](https://www.investors.com/news/technology/accenture-stock-acn-earnings-fiscal-q1-2026)\n   - Softer revenue guidance despite AI bookings growth; federal spending cuts (e.g., DOGE/Trump policies).[[11]](https://www.tikr.com/blog/accenture-stock-is-down-23-since-late-2025-heres-what-acns-latest-earnings-mean)[[12]](https://www.investopedia.com/here-is-how-much-accenture-stock-is-expected-to-move-after-earnings-acn-q2-fy2026-11926979)[[13]](https://phemex.com/academy/accenture-acn-stock-2026)\n   - Stock hit 5-year lows near $187.[[1]](https://www.macrotrends.net/stocks/charts/ACN/accenture/stock-price-history)\n3. **Positives:** Resilient dividends (15+ years growth, ~$6.52 annualized), recent earnings beats, and AI-related bookings surging. Trading near 52-week lows, potentially undervalued vs. historical P/E (~28 avg).[[14]](https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ACN)[[15]](https://seekingalpha.com/news/4566254-accenture-falls-despite-q2-beat-q3-revenue-outlook-misses-estimates)[[16]](https://www.investing.com/equities/accenture-ltd-dividends)\n4. **Portfolio Note:** Accenture is already in your portfolio. Recent drop may present a buy-low opportunity if you believe in long-term consulting/AI recovery, but caution on macro risks.\n\nIf you'd like detail